text: Daniela Campos (born 31 March 2002) is a Portuguese road racing cyclist. She was Portuguese National Time Trial Champion in 2021. She competed at the 2021 UCI Road World Championships, in the women's time trial event and women's road race event. She is a member of the Bizkaia - Durango team. == References == Category:2002 births Category:Cyclists Category:Living people
